---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Target Dossier" subtitle="// Eyes Only — Registry Reconnaissance">
  <h1 class="text-3xl text-neon-cyan glow-cyan mb-6">Target: Machiavelli Corporation</h1>

  <p class="text-fg-dim mb-8">
    Compiled from Registry field reports, intercepted comms, and whatever our people
    managed to drag out of Ironhusk before the strike broke. Incomplete. Updated as
    intel arrives.
  </p>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Profile</h2>
    <p>
      Dominant heavy-industry megacorp of Gotia VII. Origin: Forge-House Machiavelli,
      c. 500bu. Rebranded as <em>The Machiavelli Corporation</em> around 3000u after
      absorbing Dominus Arc-Smelting. Operates entirely outside Union oversight.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Leadership</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">
      CEO lineage consolidated into the <strong>Dominic family</strong> in the
      wake of the Ash Accords (c. 4400u) and has never let go. Current seat:
      <strong>Victor Dominic</strong>, operating out of Nuova Firenze — his personal
      city-state, and the most modern urban centre on a planet that otherwise
      looks like it lost a fight with its own atmosphere.
    </p>
    <p>
      Deputies, lieutenants, and middle management rotate with depressing
      regularity. The Dominics do not.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Known Assets</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-fg-dim space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Planetary mineral rights.</strong> Claimed unilaterally under the
        Ash Accords. Legally dubious under Union charter, practically absolute on
        the ground. Every independent miner-clan that disagreed was either crushed
        or absorbed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The Forge-Belt.</strong> Continent-spanning refineries and
        fortified arcologies straddling the equator. Machiavelli's productive
        spine — where the original Forge-House set up shop after the Great Vein
        Collapse, and where the corporation still makes its money.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Nuova Firenze.</strong> Victor Dominic's crown jewel. Gleaming,
        heavily surveilled, largely sealed to outsiders. Almost certainly hosts
        the executive command tier of the mainframe.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Ironhusk Foundry.</strong> Trench-city anchor in the Deep Trenches.
        Site of the Deep Trench Strike — miners took a Machiavelli base hostage
        over wages and quality of life; Registry lancers under Sgt Stoneboot broke
        it by force. Operations resumed within the week. The dead did not.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Lung-rot treatment monopoly.</strong> Until recently, Machiavelli
        controlled the entire supply of the only medicine that keeps deep-trench
        miners alive past fifty. Priced to extract, not to cure. The single
        most-cited grievance in Gravel Gault's Registry broadcasts.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>IPS-Northstar exclusive freight contract.</strong> Signed 4701u.
        Machiavelli goods ride IPS-N lanes off-world; nothing moves that
        Machiavelli doesn't manifest.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Private Harrison Armory stockpile.</strong> Publicly, Machiavelli
        protests Armory's orbital presence. Privately, they buy its ordnance. Draw
        your own conclusions.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The mainframe.</strong> Location classified at Registry level.
        Objective of the operation. That's why you're here.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Grievances</h2>
    <p>
      Too many to list. Start with lung-rot medication pricing. Finish with the Deep
      Trench Strike. Somewhere in the middle is every miner-clan they crushed on the
      way up.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
